arts.ttl: Loïs Openda strike secures victory for RB Leipzig over Eintracht Frankfurt
arts.sum: RB Leipzig secured a hard-fought 2-1 win over Eintracht Frankfurt, with goals from Šeško and Openda once again proving to be the undoing of Dino Toppmöller's side in what was a thrilling Bundesliga encounter. The match burst into life from the opening whistle, with Christoph Baumgartner having a goal disallowed due to Loïs Openda being offside in the build-up.

arts.ttl: Openda helps Leipzig in narrow win over Eintracht Frankfurt
arts.sum: RB Leipzig beat Eintracht Frankfurt in narrow fashion on Sunday during matchday 14 in the Bundesliga thanks to a second half Loïs Openda goal.
